# Project Phases
## SEO-First Local HVAC Website

---

## Overview

This document defines the **end-to-end delivery phases** for building an **SEO-first website for a local HVAC company**.

The phases are ordered intentionally.  
Each phase builds on the previous one and introduces new responsibilities only when the foundation is stable.

This document is **strategy and execution-oriented**, not implementation-level.  
Each phase will later be expanded into its own detailed specification.

---

## Phase 0 — Product & SEO Strategy Lock

### Purpose
Define **what the website must achieve** before any technical or design decisions are made.

### Focus
- Business goals and success criteria
- SEO strategy at a conceptual level
- Page types required for local HVAC SEO
- Canonical URL philosophy

### Outcomes
- Clear agreement on project goals
- No ambiguity about what pages exist or why
- SEO direction locked before build

---

## Phase 1 — Technical Foundation

### Purpose
Create a **clean, modern technical baseline** with no legacy assumptions.

### Focus
- Project scaffolding
- Framework and tooling setup
- Clear folder and responsibility boundaries
- Build and development stability

### Outcomes
- Fresh project with predictable structure
- Styling intentionally minimal
- No business logic or SEO rules yet

---

## Phase 2 — Content Model & Data Architecture

### Purpose
Define **what the website is made of**, independent of layout or design.

### Focus
- Core content entities (services, locations, reviews, FAQs, etc.)
- Relationships between entities
- Ownership of data and source of truth
- Slug and identity rules

### Outcomes
- Content can scale without code changes
- No duplication of business information
- Clear mental model of site data

---

## Phase 3 — Routing & URL Architecture

### Purpose
Implement the **SEO backbone** of the site.

### Focus
- Canonical URL patterns
- Page types and route structure
- Service, location, and service-location coverage
- Predictable and scalable routing logic

### Outcomes
- All SEO-critical pages exist
- URLs are deterministic and stable
- No special-case or ad-hoc routing rules

---

## Phase 4 — Baseline Page Rendering

### Purpose
Render real content correctly across all page types.

### Focus
- Page templates per content type
- Semantic HTML structure
- Logical internal linking
- Crawlability and indexability

### Outcomes
- Search engines can understand the site
- Users can navigate logically
- Content renders without visual polish

---

## Phase 5 — UI System & Layout Rules

### Purpose
Introduce **consistency and control** into the UI without premature branding.

### Focus
- Reusable layout primitives
- Button and card systems
- Spacing and typography rules
- Prevention of one-off styles

### Outcomes
- UI consistency across all pages
- Centralised styling decisions
- Faster development without visual drift

---

## Phase 6 — Branding & Conversion Optimisation

### Purpose
Align the site visually with the brand and optimise for lead generation.

### Focus
- Brand colours and typography
- Visual hierarchy and trust signals
- Calls to action and conversion paths
- Mobile-first refinement

### Outcomes
- Professional, credible appearance
- Clear conversion pathways
- Strong first impression for local customers

---

## Phase 7 — SEO Refinement & Local Signals

### Purpose
Turn a strong foundation into a **high-performing local SEO asset**.

### Focus
- Metadata strategy
- Structured data and schema
- Internal linking optimisation
- Local relevance reinforcement

### Outcomes
- Improved indexation and rankings
- Eligibility for rich results
- Strong local SEO signals

---

## Phase 8 — Performance, QA & Launch

### Purpose
Launch a stable, fast, and measurable website.

### Focus
- Performance auditing
- Cross-device testing
- Analytics and conversion tracking
- Launch readiness

### Outcomes
- Confident public launch
- No critical technical issues
- Measurement in place for iteration

---

## Phase 9 — Growth & Scale

### Purpose
Evolve the website into a **compounding SEO and lead-generation asset**.

### Focus
- Expansion of services and locations
- Ongoing content creation
- Conversion optimisation
- Continuous SEO improvement

### Outcomes
- Scalable growth without re-architecture
- Increased organic visibility
- Long-term business value

---

## Guiding Principle

> Each phase should reduce ambiguity, not introduce it.  
> Progress is measured by **stability and clarity**, not speed.


This document is read-only during execution and must not be edited to reflect progress or scope changes.
